2 hot bars, 1 dessert bar, and an ice cream freezer.

How many items do you have?
There are about 40 items on the buffet.

Lunch Buffet menu items:
Fried Rice, Lo Mein, General Taso's Chicken, Chow Mei Fun (Rice Noodles), Pepper Steak w. Onion, Chicken w. Broccoli, Chef's Potatoes, Pineapple Chicken, Sauteed Mushroom, Mac n Cheese, Baked Seafood, Scallion Pork, Sauteed String Bean, Peanut Butter Chicken, Japanese Chicken, Hibachi Chicken.
Sweet & Sour Chicken, Crab Rangoon, Baked Potatoes, Sweet Donuts, Chicken Teriyaki, Fried Dumplings , Chicken Wings, Egg Roll, Seafood Roll, BBQ Beef Ball, and Bake Stuffed Clam.
Hot & Sour Soup, Egg Drop Soup, and Wonton Soup
Sushi, Egg, Salad, pudding, cake and a variety of fruits.

Dinner Buffet Menu item difference:
There are more seafood items on the dinner buffet compared to the lunch buffet. Such as Steamed Shrimp and Mussels, Baked Mussels, Garlic Flavored Shrimp, Fried baby Shrimp, Seafood Casserole and Salmon. We also have Coconut chicken and Honey chicken too.

Do you have any Sushi on the Buffet?
We do, but it's very limited with choices. We do not have any raw fish for sushi. We have California Roll, Cucumber and cream cheese roll, and Smashed Salmon Roll.

Are there any American dish or dishes that kids would like to eat on the Buffet?
We have Mac and Cheese, chicken wings, chicken teriyaki, chicken fingers, and many other things at the dessert bar.

Study Guide

Crown Palace 

Crown Palace is a full time restaurant meaning that  take all their calls .

The hours of operation are: - Sunday: Noon-10:30pm

  • Monday-Thursday: 11-11pm

  • Friday and Saturday: 11-11:30 pm 

They accept cash and credit card and for credit card there has to be a minimum of $10. for credit card only Master and Visa and if they purchase less than $10 and want to pay with credit card, charge $0.25.

The default size is small.

The Moo Shu Dish does not come with rice.

When a customer does not want vegetables on the entree you must press the button ( Entree no Veg) – and it will charge the customer $1.

Ex; Moo Goo Gai Pan

No mushroom- charge $1

The lunch special is from 11-3pm and it comes with pork fried rice and egg roll or soda or soup.

The dinner combination is all day and it comes with pork fried rice and egg roll or soda or soup.

For non busy hours, pick up is 10-15 minutes and for busy hours is 15-25 minutes.

For non busy hours, delivery is 20-25 minutes and for busy hours is 25-30 minutes.

The minimum of purchase for delivery is $5 and there is no delivery fee.

Take a look at the addresses and be familiar with them.

They have roast pork and roast pork end in the appetizer.

They also have single piece of spare rib, They also have boiled wonton.

They have chicken tempura and edamame in the appetizer section.

They also have the chicken tempura in the fried specialties, and you have the choice to get it with ff, any kind of fried rice or Lo Mein.

They also have a section of Thai dishes, and it does not come with rice.

They also have a section called Chinese dishes that is for when a Chinese customer calls to place a an order the restaurant gives them a discount and they have to press on the Chinese dish button.

The coupon does not apply for lunch special.

For this restaurant they have more kinds of soup for ex; Yagamein, Ho Fun Soup, and Mai Fun soup.

In the Vegetable healthy dish section they have a section that is focused on tofu/ bean curd dishes.
